[3] California (San Joaquin county)
Date: Mon 21 Aug 2017
Source: The Horse [edited]
http://www.thehorse.com/articles/39577/seventh-california-horse-tests-positive-for-wnv


California animal health officials have confirmed an additional case of West Nile virus (WNV) in a horse in that state. "On [18 Aug 2017], an unvaccinated yearling Warmblood filly in San Joaquin County displaying severe neurologic signs was confirmed positive for WNV," said a statement from the California Department of Food and Agriculture (CDFA). "Due to the severity of clinical signs the filly was euthanized.

"For 2017, a total of 7 horses have been confirmed positive for WNV," the CDFA continued. "The positive horses were located in Glenn, Contra Costa, Fresno, Kern (2), Riverside, and San Joaquin counties. 5 horses were unvaccinated and 2 horses had unknown vaccination status. 5 horses died or were euthanized and 2 horses are recovering."

